ews, colonial subjects, homosexuals, women. Sanos argues that these intellectuals offered an "aesthetics of hate," reinventing a language of far-right nationalism by appealing to the realm of beauty and the sublime for political solutions. By acknowledging the constitutive relationship of antisemitism and colonial racism at the heart of these canonical writers' nationalism, this book makes us rethink how aesthetics and politics function, how race is imagined and defined, how gender structured far-right thought, and how we conceive of French intellectualism and fascism.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 15. Sep 2020) 0aAntisemitismxHistoryx20th centuryxFrance. 0aAntisemitismzFrancexHistoryy20th century. 0aFascist aestheticsxHistoryx20th centuryxFrance. 0aFascist aestheticszFrancexHistoryy20th century. 0aMasculinityxHistoryx20th centuryxFrance. 0aMasculinityzFrancexHistoryy20th century. 0aPolitics and literaturexHistoryx20th centuryxFrance. 0aPolitics and literaturezFrancexHistoryy20th century. 0aRadicalismxHistoryx20th centuryxFrance. 0aRadicalismzFrancexHistoryy20th century. 0aRight-wing extremistsxHistoryx20th centuryxFrance. 0aRight-wing extremistszFrancexHistoryy20th century. 7aHISTORY / Europe / France.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertSUP Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2013z978311070420440uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9780804782838zCo-access DOI >> click Walter de Gruyter40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780804782838423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780804782838.jpg  a978-3-11-070420-4  SUP Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2013c2000d2013  aGBV-deGruyter-alles